PROJECT: ClipRace — Brand Space UI refactor (frontend-first). Backend must remain correct and secure.

LOCKED STACK / LIBS (MANDATORY):
Next.js 16 App Router, React 19, Tailwind v4, shadcn/ui + Radix, lucide-react.
Supabase Auth/DB/Realtime (@supabase/ssr + supabase-js).
Stripe (MCP) + Supabase (MCP) + Shadcn MCP + GitHub integration.
UX libs to use (do not replace): framer-motion, lenis, cobe, @number-flow/react, sonner, cmdk, vaul, cva, recharts, react-hook-form, zod.
Perf dev: react-scan (dev only).

DESIGN CONSTITUTION:
- BRAND_UI_SPEC.md is the source of truth for tokens and components.
- BRAND_UI_PATTERNS.md is the source of truth for layouts/interactions/states.

CLIPRACE VISUAL IDENTITY (must be recognizable):
- Race Light (emerald edge light) for live/focus/highlight (subtle).
- Track Pattern (subtle track texture) in select panels/headers (2–4% opacity).
- Clip Notch (minimal cut-corner) for premium surfaces (KPI hero, key panels).
Accent rule: emerald visible area must remain under 10% per screen.
Glass: only for shell/overlays (topbar, command palette). Not for all cards.

ARCHITECTURE / OWNERSHIP:
- Brand-specific UI components MUST live in: src/components/brand-ui/*
- Brand pages MUST live in: src/app/brand/**
- Pages compose brand-ui components; avoid one-off markup and ad-hoc styling.

DATA & PERFORMANCE:
- Prefer RPC/views for aggregates (avoid heavy JS aggregation and huge .in([...]) lists).
- Realtime filters must match actual schema (no phantom columns).
- Promise.all for independent fetches. Skeletons to prevent CLS.
- Prefer reduced motion: respect prefers-reduced-motion.
- framer-motion and lenis must not be imported globally if avoidable; isolate them.

SECURITY:
- CSRF tokens must be crypto-strong; never Math.random fallback.
- Messages thread creation must verify: brand owns contest AND creator is related to contest.
- Rate limiting: key by (userId + ip + ua); avoid spoofable IP headers unless platform headers.

UX QUALITY BAR:
- 1 primary CTA per screen.
- Premium Loading/Empty/Error states everywhere.
- Use sonner for toasts.
- Use cmdk for global command palette.
- Use vaul drawers for mobile detail panels.
